<TITLE> Sadi takes over as BFF general secretary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 15 (bdnews24.com)  Al Musabbir Sadi became the first paid general secretary of the Bangladesh Football Federation when he took over the post on Wednesday. Under the new FIFA and AFC guidelines, the Kazi Salahuddin-led executive committee has taken a step towards professionalism by appointing a salaried general secretary, who will look after the administrative functions as well as execute decisions of the committee. The BFF earlier had an elected general secretary who served on a voluntary basis, however, FIFA and AFC asked the BFF to appoint a professional secretary. The appointment of the general secretary came just a year after the Salahuddin-led executive committee assumed power in April 2008. "It is a new job for me as well as being challenging. But I'm confident to do the job successfully with the help of everybody," said Sadi, a former senior sports journalist. Sadi said that his first task was to create bridge between the executive committee and the different sub-committees. bd
